posts.name: Sreyan Das
posts.cooked: I would go as far to say that cameras in this game for the auto period are almost required. Sure, you could through testing and iteration write plays that work good on your field, but without a camera to align to a tag I really don’t see how you ensure consistency across fields ( not to mention align to tag makes testing plays infinitely easier and also raises their ceiling)

posts.name: lobrien
posts.cooked:
I really like that idea. The highly linear poles should be easy targets for classic CV approaches and the reef geometry is pretty perfect for introductory SLAM.

One significant caution is that looking upwards in competitions can be tricky due to stadium lighting. During Steamworks we had an auto that aligned on a ceiling light and fired a beautiful arc of balls clear out of the arena.
